name: Citrine Spear Magick Wand
description:
one of a kind, 18 1/2 inches long, hand carved, sanded and oiled wild cherry branch as a base, citrine crystal tip, fastened with black and silky orange thread, 1 spiral shell and 1 tigers eye cube. finished off with a handmade tag, signed, named and dated on the back.

should be treated as art/artifact or put to use by a practicing magician or witch.

name: Red Bird Magick Wand
description:
one of a kind, a little over 16 inches long, hand carved, sanded and oiled wild cherry branch as a base, quartz crystal tip, fastened with black and silky scarlet red thread, 1 red coral carved bird bead and 1 carnelian chip with a small cardinal feather. finished off with a handmade tag, signed, named and dated on the back.

should be treated as art/artifact or put to use by a practicing magician or witch.

name: Egyptian Blue Gypsy Necklace
description:
110 inches long, sterling silver clasp, various modern and vintage blue seed beads, vintage glass triangle focal beads, turquoise chips and vintage blue glass sphere beads. finished off with a handmade tag signed and dated on the back.

versatile. one of a kind.

name: Atom Bomb Gypsy Necklace
description:
102 inches long, sterling silver clasp, multicolor seed beads, vintage navy blue plastic focal beads. finished off with a handmade tag signed and dated on the back.

versatile. one of a kind.
